cards.desc:
Instructions
--------------

* Saute onion, fennel, carrots on med-hi in olive oil until onions are translucent

* add salt and pepper to taste (we usually put quite a bit of salt)

cards.name: Orange Mac & Cheese
cards.desc:
## Instructions

Start heating water to boil for pasta. Meanwhile put carrots in small pot with garlic, tomato, and water. When the carrots are tender enough to poke with a fork, take off head and blend the contents of the pot with the canola oil until smooth. When maccaroni are cooked, drain and mix in carrot blend. Place in casserole and top with cheese and breadcrumbs. Low broil for four minutes or until cheese starts sizzling.

cards.name: Beet Risotto
cards.desc:
Inspired by a dish from a Pub in Pointe St-Charles. Our first version is missing some fanciness like lots of butter and parmesan, but still highly tasty and sweet. The other thing the pub did was sprinkle fried bread crumbs on top. That was delicious, but we replaced those bread curmbs with pisci l'ovo (recipe coming soon), which is basically eggs and breadcrumbs mixed together and fried like pancakes.

## Instructions

In a large pot, stirfry onions and beat cubes until they start to caramelize, then stir in the rice until it looks translucent. Then add salt, broth or water and cook rice as instructed on its packaging.

Meanwhile, to make the sauce in a sauce pan, saute the beat, garlic, potato, and onion chuncks. Cover with 3/4 of the way with broth or water. Cook till ingredients are soft enough to blend. Blend to pur√© consistency. Mix butter in.

Serve rice with copious amounts of sauce on top, and the piscil'ovo on top of that.

cards.name: Vanilla cake
cards.desc:
https://sugarspunrun.com/vanilla-cake-recipe/

## Instructions

Preheat oven to 350F (177C) and prepare two deep 8" round cake pans** by lining the bottoms with parchment paper and lightly greasing the sides. Set aside. 

In the bowl of a stand mixer (or in a large bowl using an electric mixer) cream together the butter, canola oil and sugar until creamy and well-combined.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Stir in vanilla extract.

In a separate, medium-sized bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt.

Using a spatula and gently hand-mixing, alternate adding flour mixture and buttermilk to the butter mixture, starting and ending with flour mixture and mixing until just combined after each addition.¬† The batter should be smooth and completely combined, but avoid over-mixing.

Evenly divide batter into your prepared cake pans, and bake on 350F (175C) for 30-35 minutes.¬† When the cake is done, the surface should spring back to the touch and a toothpick inserted in the center should come out mostly clean with few moist crumbs (no wet batter).

Allow cakes to cool in their cake pans for 10-15 minutes before inverting onto cooling rack to cool completely before frosting.

Frost cake using my chocolate frosting and decorate with sprinkles (if desired).

### Notes

*You may substitute vegetable oil instead

**You may use 9" cake pans instead, but watch the cooking time as they may need less time in the oven.

How to Make Into Vanilla Cupcakes:

Fill cupcake liners no more than 3/4 of the way full. Bake on 350F for 17-18 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out with a few moist crumbs or clean. This recipe will make approximately 24 cupcakes.

cards.name: Olive Oil
cards.desc:
## Very fast overview of olive oil labelling 

"Virgin" means that only mechanical means were used to extract the oil.

"Extra-virgin" is judged to taste better than "Virgin" by experts in blind taste test.

Oils labelled Pure, Classic, Light, Extra-Light, or simply Olive oil are actually _refined olive oil_. That is to say virgin olive oil refined using charcoal or other chemical or mechanical means in order remove taste or smell that is judged to be too poor for human consumption. This oil is completely flavourless, and is therefore mixed with small amounts of virgin olive oil.

Cooking olive oil at temperatures higher than 200C (e.g: deep frying), will deteriorate the taste, in which case it is sufficient to use refined olive oil.
